title: Merced River at Henderson Park
description: “Today, Henderson Park, the restored area situated along the north bank of the Merced River in eastern Merced County, offers opportunities for picnicking, fishing, and other river recreation. In the early 2000’s, the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service teamed with Merced County, Cramer Fish Sciences, and the local community of Snelling to restore channel form and function on the Merced River at Henderson Park.”
copyright: by Jesse Anderson, Sr., Cramer Fish Sciences for USFWS - Public Domain

title: St. Johns Catholic Church
description: Catholic Mission in Hopeton, CA near Snelling. Hopeton is where John Muir resided in a sheep ranch from the fall of 1868 to the spring 1869 prior to his trip to Yosemite described in "My First Summer in the Sierra"
copyright: Courtesy of Randy Graham via http://www.usgwarchives.net/
